cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a method for improving their robustness and compactness through weight pruning and regularization techniques. This topic is relevant to machine learning, computer vision, and artificial intelligence, as well as security and cryptography.
